annotation: Tang Kristensen never published this amusing little statement, perhaps because he considered it obscene. He likely wrote it down as a way to capture dialect pronunciations, given the spelling of the words in the field diaries.
danish_manuscript: Dem i Duurstryp de laver djer Børn i Mørke.
english_manuscript: The people in Duurstryp they make their children in the dark.
english_publication: Unpublished version reads: The people in Duurstryp they make their children in the dark.
